You step through this program in a debugger, stepping *over* every line in `main`. What does the program print to stdout?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

int double_it(int n) {
    return n * 2;
}

int main() {
    int x = 5;
    int y = double_it(x);
    std::cout << y << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```

A programmer adds `std::cerr` messages to simulate what a debugger would show at each step. What does this program print to **stdout**?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

int add(int a, int b) {
    std::cerr << "[step] inside add a=" << a << " b=" << b << "\n";
    int sum = a + b;
    std::cerr << "[step] sum=" << sum << "\n";
    return sum;
}

int main() {
    int result = add(6, 9);
    std::cout << result << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```
